for this party.

275
00:26:54,779 --> 00:26:57,741
Come on, Aurora.
It's not just another party.

276
00:26:58,700 --> 00:27:01,911
It's like the rebirth of Basil.

277
00:27:01,995 --> 00:27:02,912
Beverly!

278
00:27:03,621 --> 00:27:06,082
No! Beverly…

279
00:27:06,791 --> 00:27:07,667
Beverly…

280
00:27:07,751 --> 00:27:08,585
Sir!

281
00:27:08,668 --> 00:27:11,671
The ambulance and the police
are on their way, sir.

282
00:27:11,755 --> 00:27:12,964
What's the use?

283
00:27:13,548 --> 00:27:14,841
Beverly is dead!

284
00:27:14,924 --> 00:27:16,217
My grandson is dead!

285
00:27:16,301 --> 00:27:17,218
They were killed!

286
00:27:18,636 --> 00:27:19,679
God!

287
00:27:20,472 --> 00:27:21,473
Beverly…

288
00:27:23,475 --> 00:27:26,478
- Look for the person who killed her!
- Okay, sir.

289
00:27:29,731 --> 00:27:30,857
My grandson…

290
00:27:31,566 --> 00:27:32,817
My grandson…

291
00:27:50,668 --> 00:27:52,128
Cairo, here!

292
00:27:52,212 --> 00:27:53,213
Cairo!

293
00:27:53,671 --> 00:27:54,672
Cairo, here!

294
00:28:27,497 --> 00:28:32,210
Ma'am, you can stay here. That way,
you'll be near Sir Galvan's room.

295
00:28:33,670 --> 00:28:36,297
And, ma'am, here.

296
00:28:36,381 --> 00:28:39,926
If you need anything, just call me.

297
00:28:41,177 --> 00:28:42,137
Thank you.

298
00:28:43,555 --> 00:28:44,764
Thank you.

299
00:28:44,848 --> 00:28:46,057
Okay, ma'am.

300
00:28:47,142 --> 00:28:48,393
I'll go ahead.

301
00:28:48,476 --> 00:28:49,728
Hold on.

302
00:28:49,811 --> 00:28:51,521
Can I have that?

303
00:28:57,360 --> 00:29:01,614
So that just in case someone tries
to hurt me, I can defend myself.

304
00:29:14,002 --> 00:29:15,962
Are you okay, Beverly?

305
00:29:16,045 --> 00:29:18,089
- Are you okay here?
- Of course.

306
00:29:18,423 --> 00:29:20,175
More than okay.

307
00:29:20,258 --> 00:29:21,259
Okay.

308
00:29:21,342 --> 00:29:22,510
So…

309
00:29:23,261 --> 00:29:24,846
Don't forget our agreement, okay?

310
00:29:25,805 --> 00:29:27,766
One million pesos.

311
00:29:28,767 --> 00:29:29,893
What for?

312
00:29:31,019 --> 00:29:34,481
I called you in your province

313
00:29:34,564 --> 00:29:38,818
to inform you that Sir Basil was dead.

314
00:29:39,652 --> 00:29:45,033
So, you wouldn't be here now
if it hadn't been for me.

315
00:29:46,785 --> 00:29:49,162
A million? Just for that?

316
00:29:49,245 --> 00:29:50,872
Are you a scammer?

317
00:29:51,456 --> 00:29:54,834
Don't double-cross me, Beverly.

318
00:29:57,378 --> 00:30:00,006
Because I'm different when I get mad.

319
00:30:47,303 --> 00:30:48,388
Ma'am!

320
00:30:48,471 --> 00:30:49,806
Madam!

321
00:30:49,889 --> 00:30:51,808
Ma'am Aurora!

322
00:30:51,891 --> 00:30:53,142
- What?
- Ma'am!

323
00:30:53,226 --> 00:30:56,271
Madam!

324
00:30:56,354 --> 00:30:58,189
Ma'am Aurora! Madam!

325
00:30:58,273 --> 00:31:00,233
What's with you? My goodness!

326
00:31:01,276 --> 00:31:02,485
What?

327
00:31:02,569 --> 00:31:04,362
Your voice is so annoying!

328
00:31:04,445 --> 00:31:05,947
I'm sorry!

329
00:31:06,030 --> 00:31:09,367
I'm sorry, but Ms. Beverly
has had an emergency.

330
00:31:09,450 --> 00:31:11,953
So what are you waiting for?
Bring her to the hospital!

331
00:31:12,036 --> 00:31:13,413
It's too late.

332
00:31:13,496 --> 00:31:15,039
She's dead.

333
00:31:15,623 --> 00:31:17,333
Oh my God, what?

334
00:31:17,417 --> 00:31:19,085
Someone stabbed her.

335
00:31:20,211 --> 00:31:21,921
Who stabbed her?

336
00:31:22,338 --> 00:31:25,717
I don't know,
but they're looking for the killer now.

337
00:31:25,800 --> 00:31:30,597
And, madam, they said that
the killer is still in the area.

338
00:31:34,309 --> 00:31:35,935
Where's Samantha?

339
00:31:36,019 --> 00:31:37,312
Let's look for Sam!

340
00:31:37,395 --> 00:31:38,605
Go, go, go, Angie!

341
00:31:38,688 --> 00:31:41,482
Is Ma'am Samantha there?

342
00:31:41,566 --> 00:31:43,359
Oh my God.

343
00:31:43,985 --> 00:31:46,821
Our Father who art in heaven,
hallowed be Thy Name.

344
00:31:46,905 --> 00:31:50,241
Thy kingdom come, Thy will be done,
on earth as it is in heaven.

345
00:31:50,325 --> 00:31:52,452
Why is there still a lot of blood?

346
00:31:54,203 --> 00:31:55,663
Bev is still moving.

347
00:31:56,497 --> 00:31:58,291
Her hand is still moving.

348
00:32:00,752 --> 00:32:03,212
- It's called rigor mortis.
- What?

349
00:32:04,339 --> 00:32:08,217
When a person dies, their body
makes unnecessary movements.

350
00:32:09,385 --> 00:32:14,474
The muscles soften and the body goes limp,

351
00:32:15,600 --> 00:32:19,562
and the liquids from the dead
are also released.

352
00:32:19,646 --> 00:32:21,522
- Louie.
- What the heck, man?

353
00:32:35,036 --> 00:32:37,580
Be quiet there and just help me pray.

354
00:32:37,664 --> 00:32:38,957
What's with you?

355
00:32:39,040 --> 00:32:41,000
Hail Mary, full of grace,
the Lord is with thee.

356
00:32:41,084 --> 00:32:44,128
Blessed art thou amongst women
and blessed is the fruit…

357
00:32:44,212 --> 00:32:45,922
Hey, hey, where are you going?

358
00:32:46,005 --> 00:32:47,131
Just stay here!

359
00:32:47,215 --> 00:32:49,300
The killer is on the loose!

360
00:32:49,384 --> 00:32:51,719
That's the thing.
The killer is on the loose.

361
00:32:51,803 --> 00:32:53,346
They might hurt George.

362
00:32:53,888 --> 00:32:55,723
- Ward…
- Hey, Ward!

363
00:32:55,807 --> 00:32:57,892
Ward, come back here!

364
00:32:57,976 --> 00:32:59,936
My God, this kid.

365
00:33:00,019 --> 00:33:02,981
Lord, Lord, please,
Lord, help them.

366
00:33:03,856 --> 00:33:07,527
Protect this household from evil spirits!

367
00:33:07,610 --> 00:33:11,823
Protect this household from evil spirits!

368
00:33:12,573 --> 00:33:16,619
- Protect this household from evil spirits.
- I'll just go to Mother.

369
00:33:16,703 --> 00:33:17,954
- Hold on.
- No, Sam!

370
00:33:18,037 --> 00:33:21,124
- Protect this household from…
- You stay here.

371
00:33:21,207 --> 00:33:22,542
I already told you.

372
00:33:22,625 --> 00:33:24,252
Your mother is safe.

373
00:33:26,295 --> 00:33:31,676
No one will leave this room unless
we are assured that it's safe outside.

374
00:33:31,759 --> 00:33:32,969
Do you understand?

375
00:33:33,511 --> 00:33:34,721
Yes, madam.

376
00:33:35,388 --> 00:33:39,642
Amando, anyone who tries
to enter that door,

377
00:33:39,726 --> 00:33:42,228
don't hesitate to shoot them.

378
00:34:19,849 --> 00:34:24,520
Protect this household from evil spirits.

379
00:34:25,104 --> 00:34:28,858
Protect this household from evil spirits!

380
00:34:28,941 --> 00:34:31,944
- Protect this household…
- Come with me, Ma'am Rebecca.

381
00:34:32,028 --> 00:34:33,571
…from evil spirits!

382
00:34:33,654 --> 00:34:34,822
Who's there?

383
00:34:36,491 --> 00:34:37,617
Who's there?

384
00:34:40,119 --> 00:34:41,329
Who's that?

385
00:34:51,798 --> 00:34:52,924
Mother!

386
00:34:59,722 --> 00:35:02,600
Mother! Hold on, hold on!

387
00:35:02,683 --> 00:35:03,768
My God, Mercy!

388
00:35:03,851 --> 00:35:05,895
We almost shot you!

389
00:35:05,978 --> 00:35:08,356
I thought you were inside your room!

390
00:35:08,439 --> 00:35:10,566
I was worried about Sam.

391
00:35:11,359 --> 00:35:12,819
Mother, come here.

392
00:35:12,902 --> 00:35:14,403
- What happened?
- Are you okay?

393
00:35:14,487 --> 00:35:16,364
I'm okay. How about you?

394
00:35:17,073 --> 00:35:18,324
What's happening?

395
00:35:18,783 --> 00:35:20,034
Mother.

396
00:35:20,118 --> 00:35:21,244
Sam.

397
00:35:22,078 --> 00:35:23,204
My God.

398
00:35:23,788 --> 00:35:25,873
I'm so sorry, Sam.

399
00:35:36,259 --> 00:35:37,135
Go, go, go.

400
00:35:38,636 --> 00:35:40,221
Thank you. Thank you.

401
00:35:40,304 --> 00:35:42,306
Amando, what is it?

402
00:35:43,516 --> 00:35:45,184
Everyone is safe to go outside.

403
00:36:16,257 --> 00:36:17,300
Ma'am Rebecca?

404
00:36:18,342 --> 00:36:19,552
What are you doing here?

405
00:36:23,222 --> 00:36:24,724
Well…

406
00:36:26,184 --> 00:36:31,606
I was bothered when you kept
asking about Papa last night,

407
00:36:31,689 --> 00:36:37,195
so I came here to clear things out.

408
00:36:43,784 --> 00:36:45,328
But I saw that.

409
00:36:54,420 --> 00:36:57,131
That's what Bev's killer was wearing.

410
00:37:04,222 --> 00:37:05,223
Was it you…

411
00:37:07,892 --> 00:37:09,602
who killed Bev,

412
00:37:11,270 --> 00:37:12,271
Jerico?

413
00:37:20,571 --> 00:37:22,323
Ma'am Rebecca, no.

414
00:37:22,406 --> 00:37:24,283
I had nothing to do with
what happened to Ma'am Bev.

415
00:37:31,374 --> 00:37:32,500
Ma'am Rebecca…

416
00:37:32,875 --> 00:37:34,043
- Please, ma'am.
- Let me go.

417
00:37:34,126 --> 00:37:35,753
Okay. Okay. Ma'am.

418
00:37:35,836 --> 00:37:36,712
Ma'am.

419
00:37:37,213 --> 00:37:38,256
Ma'am, okay.

420
00:37:39,173 --> 00:37:41,717
Okay, if you have doubts about me,
have me investigated.

421
00:37:42,343 --> 00:37:44,971
You can even give that hoodie
to Sergeant Casas.

422
00:37:45,846 --> 00:37:47,807
But please, listen to me first.

423
00:37:47,890 --> 00:37:49,892
What else do I have to listen to?

424
00:37:52,270 --> 00:37:55,231
The reason I'm asking about
your papa is because…

425
00:37:57,817 --> 00:37:58,859
Because?

426
00:37:59,360 --> 00:38:00,361
Why?

427
00:38:04,740 --> 00:38:06,492
I'll talk to the investigator.

428
00:38:07,451 --> 00:38:08,452
What the--

429
00:38:08,536 --> 00:38:09,954
I am a Palacios.

430
00:38:13,124 --> 00:38:15,001
I am the son of Rodolfo Palacios.

431
00:38:16,544 --> 00:38:17,628
Your father.

432
00:38:19,422 --> 00:38:21,090
We're siblings, Ma'am Rebecca.

433
00:38:22,550 --> 00:38:23,884
No, that's not true.

434
00:38:26,178 --> 00:38:27,263
What are you saying?

435
00:38:31,934 --> 00:38:33,269
What's that?

436
00:38:33,352 --> 00:38:34,312
Look at it.

437
00:38:53,706 --> 00:38:54,749
No…

438
00:39:02,256 --> 00:39:03,341
No…

439
00:39:13,225 --> 00:39:14,685
Papa…

440
00:39:16,437 --> 00:39:17,772
This is Papa.

441
00:39:20,232 --> 00:39:22,943
I am the little boy he is carrying.

442
00:39:29,742 --> 00:39:30,701
No…

443
00:39:32,203 --> 00:39:34,789
I miss Papa's voice.

444
00:39:59,939 --> 00:40:01,565
How did you learn that song?

445
00:40:02,942 --> 00:40:05,361
Papa made that song for me.

446
00:40:06,362 --> 00:40:07,947
My mother memorized it

447
00:40:08,030 --> 00:40:12,535
and she often sang that to me after

448
00:40:13,119 --> 00:40:14,787
Papa didn't return.

449
00:40:18,082 --> 00:40:21,168
<i>Hush, my baby</i>

450
00:40:22,044 --> 00:40:23,921
<i>Don't you cry</i>

451
00:40:25,339 --> 00:40:28,801
<i>In a starry night</i>

452
00:40:30,094 --> 00:40:31,971
<i>Look up at the sky</i>

453
00:40:35,891 --> 00:40:37,726
<i>Spread your wings</i>

454
00:40:39,186 --> 00:40:45,943
<i>Spread your wings and start to fly</i>

455
00:40:48,612 --> 00:40:51,574
<i>Go to sleep</i>

456
00:40:53,033 --> 00:40:58,414
<i>With my lullaby</i>

457
00:41:10,801 --> 00:41:12,178
You know what?

458
00:41:12,261 --> 00:41:14,638
Papa used to sing that song for me too.

459
00:41:17,349 --> 00:41:19,477
But as far as I remember…

460
00:41:22,229 --> 00:41:24,899
only the two of us knew about that.

461
00:41:36,911 --> 00:41:41,957
So, the dream I had of two new members
of the Palacios family…

462
00:41:42,041 --> 00:41:47,379
You're the second Palacios,
not Bev's baby.

463
00:41:49,882 --> 00:41:52,009
Oh my God.

464
00:41:52,092 --> 00:41:53,260
Just…

465
00:41:54,887 --> 00:41:56,889
I can't believe that I have a brother.

466
00:41:59,725 --> 00:42:01,727
So…

467
00:42:03,020 --> 00:42:05,564
I'll call you "big brother"?

468
00:42:06,899 --> 00:42:08,442
Oh, please, don't call me ma'am.

469
00:42:08,526 --> 00:42:10,069
Don't call me "ma'am," okay?

470
00:42:11,946 --> 00:42:17,785
Wait, yes! I should prepare
a welcome party for you!

471
00:42:17,868 --> 00:42:18,744
Don't!

472
00:42:18,827 --> 00:42:20,287
Why?

473
00:42:21,080 --> 00:42:23,499
No one should know that we're siblings,

474
00:42:23,582 --> 00:42:25,626
especially not Ma'am Aurora.

475
00:42:25,709 --> 00:42:27,461
Because

476
00:42:27,545 --> 00:42:29,630
she might do to me
what she did to my mother.

477
00:42:30,756 --> 00:42:32,841
What did Auntie Aurora do to her?

478
00:42:38,514 --> 00:42:40,224
When she found out

479
00:42:41,183 --> 00:42:43,227
that my mother was Papa's girlfriend,

480
00:42:44,353 --> 00:42:46,689
she made it look like my mother
stole from the company.

481
00:42:47,898 --> 00:42:48,983
Auntie did that?

482
00:42:49,483 --> 00:42:50,693
Yes.

483
00:42:52,069 --> 00:42:54,780
Papa helped her escape
just before she could get arrested

484
00:42:54,863 --> 00:42:57,658
and hid her in the provinces.

485
00:42:57,741 --> 00:42:58,826
So…

486
00:43:00,911 --> 00:43:02,496
Wait.

487
00:43:02,580 --> 00:43:04,415
You mean to say…

488
00:43:06,041 --> 00:43:09,878
the reason you're here is because you're
seeking revenge on Auntie?

489
00:43:09,962 --> 00:43:11,338
What?

490
00:43:11,422 --> 00:43:12,673
No.

491
00:43:12,756 --> 00:43:14,091
I'm looking for Papa.

492
00:43:14,174 --> 00:43:15,884
But Papa is dead.

493
00:43:15,968 --> 00:43:17,469
He died a long time ago.

494
00:43:17,553 --> 00:43:18,887
Rebecca, no.

495
00:43:19,680 --> 00:43:21,890
I've been suspecting for a long time
that he's still alive.

496
00:43:22,349 --> 00:43:24,310
I opened his coffin and it was empty.

497
00:43:35,529 --> 00:43:36,614
What?

498
00:44:26,664 --> 00:44:31,251
<i>A gold digger can bury herself</i>
<i>if she digs in too deep.</i>

499
00:44:31,335 --> 00:44:34,713
So, others should be careful.

500
00:44:34,797 --> 00:44:36,382
If you dig for gold,

501
00:44:36,465 --> 00:44:40,678
sometimes what you end up seeing
is the Angel of Death's sickle.

502
00:44:40,761 --> 00:44:42,221
NEXT EPISODE

503
00:44:42,304 --> 00:44:44,139
<i>Stabbing was the method of killing,</i>

504
00:44:44,223 --> 00:44:45,933
but the murder weapon is missing.

505
00:44:46,016 --> 00:44:49,853
Sir, did you find a knife
in Ms. Beverly's things?

506
00:44:49,937 --> 00:44:51,021
No, why?

507
00:44:51,105 --> 00:44:54,983
Peter, didn't Ms. Beverly ask for
the knife in the pig's head?

508
00:44:55,067 --> 00:44:57,277
Maybe that was used to kill her.

509
00:44:57,361 --> 00:44:59,071
<i>What did you do to my brother?</i>

510
00:44:59,154 --> 00:45:00,739
He got involved in a riot, ma'am.

511
00:45:00,823 --> 00:45:02,116
<i>I'm okay, Sam.</i>

512
00:45:02,199 --> 00:45:03,492
<i>I'm getting used to it.</i>

513
00:45:03,575 --> 00:45:04,910
Actually, I am already ready.

514
00:45:04,993 --> 00:45:06,412
Ready for what, Francis?

515
00:45:06,495 --> 00:45:07,871
I'm ready to die.

516
00:45:07,955 --> 00:45:09,915
Francis, don't say that.

517
00:45:10,416 --> 00:45:11,708
That's where I'm headed.

518
00:45:11,792 --> 00:45:13,502
<i>I have cancer, remember?</i>

519
00:45:13,585 --> 00:45:15,087
<i>That's where I'll end up.</i>

520
00:45:15,170 --> 00:45:16,755
<i>I will die too.</i>
